column5: ....Oh the shame of it all. Not my finest moment Norm.    (note to self....put Cliffy on mod Q.   )
ACK!!!!  Ok Ok Ok...maybe the the scene isn't quite how the picture shows.  I used a 5 foot rod and shakespeare reel on string with a paperclip for a hook.
I thought I could see smoke coming from down yer way.  Yer a better man then I to pose with that pinky.LOL  How did you ever get that fish through the grates?
lets see storm drain+ pink fishin pole+ walleye + Cliff= some kind of put on.... Lets see were this one goes.   Art
MAYBE HE WAS FISHING THE SLOP Art.
....You promised to keep this under your hat. Can't trust anyone these days.....
Nice to see you're in touch with your feminine side.
I've saved that pic... it'll come in handy at a later date I'm sure!!!
Now that's hardcore!
Geez Cliff.  For starting fishing a couple of years ago, don't ya think this is being just a bit rooster-y?  Rubbing it in that you can catch fish out of the sewer using a kids rod.
There is a spot in the foreground that you cant really see...the opening is a lot bigger    Figured you'd do that Glen......    Yep...you do know that spot...now keep a lid on it...
I was going to use my ice fishing rod, but that would have been over the top I think.  Plus...that Barbie rod catches lots of fish!!
Grate catch!
that looks like a "sewer sauger" to me
I don't know what is funnier, the pic or the claim by Cliff that he was thinking

Has anyone thought to mention to Cliff that the Barby rod may be a big part of the reason Bly always outfishes him? I mean it's as cute as all get out, and is a great colour for him and all, but ... well...  Cliff, confidentially, if it's a money issue, I've got a few somewhat more manly rods and reels here you could choose from. It would be great for your self-esteem to at least look like a manly fisher, even if yer wife kicks yer butt all the time on the water.  JF
Cliff i think you have issuses man !!!!!!...they have people for that you know !!.LOL..LOL..LOL..
Cliff, thanks for making my day.  GCD, I spit my drink out after reading that.
Hmmm....  Looks like a poockerel to me.  Glad to see they're making a come back in your parts.

Don't ever buy the Divorced Barbie stuff its like $400 it comes with Ken's House, Corvette,and Monthly payments  Ah this is the Cliff I know.The calm guy fishing in November with an 8 foot 6 rod.
